  &lt;p id="KQJ0cd"&gt;Samsung will trot out its next foldables and some new Galaxy AI features during the summer edition of its Galaxy Unpacked event in Paris, France, on Wednesday. You can expect a new Galaxy Z Fold 6 with a &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/28/24188017/samsung-galaxy-z-flip-fold-6-leak-renders-colors-unpacked"&gt;squarish look&lt;/a&gt; and a not-square Z Flip 6, both with &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/3/24191966/samsung-galaxy-z-fold-flip-6-spec-leak"&gt;much brighter screens and longer battery life&lt;/a&gt; than their predecessors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="grFlSh"&gt;Based on recent leaks, the company will announce new &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/20/24182744/samsung-galaxy-buds-3-leak-airpods-design"&gt;AirPods-like Galaxy Buds&lt;/a&gt; and even a &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/24/24163867/samsung-galaxy-watch7-ultra-leak-square"&gt;new squircle-shaped Galaxy Watch 7 “Ultra,”&lt;/a&gt; aimed at the Apple Watch Ultra. Keep an eye out for the Galaxy Ring, too. Rumor has it that Samsung’s new wearable smart ring &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/14/24100603/looks-like-samsung-thinks-youll-put-a-ring-on-it"&gt;went into mass production in May&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="6cZlyT"&gt;When is Samsung Galaxy Unpacked?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p id="C4dJNm"&gt;Samsung will stream Galaxy Unpacked at 6AM PT / 9AM ET on July 10th. &lt;/p&gt;
